Steps to create android project in Android studio
1. Create a project
2. Create layout xml file in res/layout folder
3. Create Activity class file for the respective layout xml
4. Register the Activity class in AndroidManifest.xml file
5. Declare start/launch activity in AndroidManifest.xml file

1. Gridview example is used in Color learning functionality. (To use gridview, an adapter is required)
2. FrameLayout example is used in Color Learning functionality because either Gridview or LinearLayout (on click of grid image) will be shown at a given point of time




